# KrishiFarms CRM Context

Indian farm operations CRM backend (procurement, ledger, workforce, fleet, rentals, finance). Org-scoped multi-tenancy, OpenAPI-first, bilingual EN/TE, INR.

## Start here

1. [AGENTS.md](../../AGENTS.md) — quick scan
2. [docs/AGENT_GUIDE.md](../../docs/AGENT_GUIDE.md) — full reference + implementation matrix

**Schema and OpenAPI are ahead of Python.** Phase 1 routes only in `app/main.py`. Verify before calling or implementing endpoints.

## Conventions

- `org_id` from JWT only — never from request body
- `APIResponse` envelope; `require_permission("resource:action")`
- Money: `Decimal` / `NUMERIC(14,2)` — never `float`
- Soft delete via `deleted_at`; ledger is immutable (reversing entries)
- Partitioned tables need partition date on ID lookups
- Module layout: `router.py` → `service.py` → `models.py` / `schemas.py`
- Register new models in `app/models.py`
- **Git / deploy:** feature branches + PR to `main` only — **never push to `main`**; production deploy starts on merge (`deploy.yml` on `push` to `main`), not on feature-branch pushes alone

## On every change

Update [docs/CHANGELOG.md](../../docs/CHANGELOG.md) and affected docs (see `maintain-agent-docs` rule).
